    <img src="https://tse2.mm.bing.net/th/id/OIP.B39-1EvwOFXOffOfIKZT0AHaEK?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain&o=7&rm=3"
        alt="Description of image" title="scenery">

    <pre>Explanation of Attributes:

src → (source) file path of the image.
Example: src="flower.png"

alt → alternative text shown if the image fails to load or for screen readers.
Example: alt="Beautiful flower"

width → sets the width of the image.
Example: width="300"

height → sets the height of the image.
Example: height="200"

title → shows text when you hover over the image.
Example: title="Rose picture"</pre>

            <img src="sun.jpg" alt="Sunset" title="Evening Sunset" width="300">
        <pre>alt attribute ka matlab hai Alternative Text.
Ye tab show hota hai jab image load na ho (ya user screen reader use kar raha ho).

Kaam:

Agar image file missing ho → to alt ka text dikhai dega.

Screen readers (blind users ke liye) image ka description padhte hain → jo alt mein hota hai.

SEO (Google search) mein bhi images ke liye helpful hota hai.</pre>
</body>

